<item>
            <title>[FLINK-8596] Custom command line code does not correctly catch errors</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-8596</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The code that is trying to load the YARN CLI is catching &lt;tt&gt;Exception&lt;/tt&gt; but if the YARN CLI cannot be loaded a &lt;tt&gt;java.lang.NoClassDefFoundError&lt;/tt&gt; is thrown: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/flink/blob/0e20b613087e1b326e05674e3d532ea4aa444bc3/flink-clients/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/client/cli/CliFrontend.java#L1067&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/flink/blob/0e20b613087e1b326e05674e3d532ea4aa444bc3/flink-clients/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/client/cli/CliFrontend.java#L1067&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This means that Flink does not work in Hadoop-free mode. We should fix this and also add an end-to-end test that verifies that Hadoop-free mode works.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
